	(415,'http://www.engadget.com/2012/09/27/xbox-music-us-pricing-leak/','US pricing leaks for incoming Xbox Music service','Engadget','27 September 2012, 12:43 pm','<p> <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2012/09/27/xbox-music-us-pricing-leak/\"><img alt=\"US pricing leaks for incoming Xbox Music service\" data-src-height=\"392\" data-src-width=\"620\" src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2012/09/xboxus.jpg\" /></a></p><p> Following those <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2012/09/26/dashboard-beta-leaks-new-xbox-music-pass-cloud-playlists-and-ea/\">British-based leaks</a> yesterday, a second mole has now offered us a glimpse at <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2012/06/04/microsoft-announces-xbox-music-coming-to-360-pcs-tablets-and/\">Xbox Music</a> pricing across the Atlantic. It looks like the Zune successor will offer a longer 30-day free trial, alongside $10 per-month and $100 annual subscriptions. Surprise -- looks like Americans are getting a better deal.</p><p>Filed under: <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/category/gaming/\" rel=\"tag\">Gaming</a>, <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/category/portable-audio-video/\" rel=\"tag\">Portable Audio/Video</a></p><p><a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2012/09/27/xbox-music-us-pricing-leak/\">US pricing leaks for incoming Xbox Music service</a> originally appeared on <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com\">Engadget</a> on Thu, 27 Sep 2012 08:43:00 EDT.  Please see our <a href=\"http://www.weblogsinc.com/feed-terms/\">terms for use of feeds</a>.</p><h6></h6><a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2012/09/27/xbox-music-us-pricing-leak/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">Permalink</a>&nbsp;<img class=\"img_label\" src=\"http://www.blogsmithmedia.com/www.engadget.com/media/post_label_VIA.gif\" alt=\"\" /><span><a href=\"http://wmpoweruser.com/xbox-music-us-pricing-also-revealed/\" target=\"_blank\">WMPoweruser</a><!--//--></span> &nbsp;|&nbsp; <img class=\"img_label\" src=\"http://www.blogsmithmedia.c