	(590,'http://www.soompi.com/2012/09/29/brown-eyed-girls-miryo-reveals-rock-version-of-dirty/','Brown Eyed Girls’ Miryo Reveals Rock Version of “Dirty”','Soompi','29 September 2012, 3:48 am','<p>The audio for the rock version of <strong>Miryo</strong>&#8216;s &#8220;<strong>Dirty</strong>&#8221; was revealed today on <strong>Brown Eyed Girls</strong>&#8216; YouTube channel.  </p>\n<p>The original version of <a href=\"http://www.soompi.com/2012/02/01/miryo-releases-full-version-music-video-of-dirty/\">&#8220;Dirty&#8221; was released in February</a> of this year and was the title track of her solo album &#8220;<strong>Miryo Aka Johoney</strong>.&#8221; </p>\n<div></div>\n<div>-</div>\n<div>Which version of the song do you prefer? The <a href=\"http://www.soompi.com/2012/02/01/miryo-releases-full-version-music-video-of-dirty/\">original </a>or this new rock version? </div>',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(591,'http://www.soompi.com/2012/09/29/rookie-group-100-releases-dance-version-mv-for-bad-boy/','Rookie Group 100% Releases Dance Version MV for “Bad Boy”','Soompi','29 September 2012, 3:19 am','<p>After making their debut last week and releasing their <a href=\"http://www.soompi.com/2012/09/18/new-boy-group-100-releases-debut-mv-bad-boy/\">music video for &#8220;<strong>Bad Boy</strong>&#8220;</a> last week, rookie group <strong>100%</strong> has now released their dance version music video.</p>\n<p>While this version shows off the same three locations (the flaming desert, a black and white room, and a bright shiny square room), the individual scenes and closeups were removed.    </p>\n<p>Created by <strong>TOP Media</strong>, they are label mates alongside established <strong>Teen Top</strong>. The members of this seven person group are <strong>Minwoo</strong> (leader), <strong>Rocky</strong>, <strong>Jonghwan</strong>, <strong>Chanyong</strong>, <strong>Changbum</strong>, <strong>Hyukjin</strong> and <strong>Sanghoon</strong>. Rocky was previously a member of TOP Media’s 2009 group <strong>Jumper</strong>.</p>\n<p>Following the release of their debut single &#8220;<strong>We 100</strong>&#8221; on September 18, they made their debut performances on the various music shows.</p>\n<div></div>',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(592,'http://www.soompi.com/2012/09/29/spica-releases-dance-practice-video-for-ill-be-there/','SPICA Releases Dance Practice for “I’ll Be There”','Soompi','29 September 2012, 1:56 am','<p>After making their comeback last week with their new single &#8220;<strong>I&#8217;ll Be There</strong>,&#8221; <strong>SPICA</strong> has now released their dance practice video.</p>\n<p>Recorded in their studio, the girls show off their choreography for this dance pop track.  </p>\n<p>While their previous songs &#8220;<strong>Potently,</strong>” “<strong>Russian Roulette,</strong>” and “<strong>Painkiller</strong>” showed off a more serious concept, &#8220;I&#8217;ll Be There&#8221; features a completely different side of SPICA.</p>\n<p>The song was co-produced song by composer Marco and Da-un Jeon and is described as “a dance pop song that mixed hip-hop beat along with the funky rhythms of the 1990s.”</p>\n<div></div>\n<p>Check out their live performance from last weekend&#8217;s episode of <strong>Inkigayo</strong>.</p>\n<div></div>',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(593,'http://www.soompi.com/2012/09/29/aoa-to-make-their-comeback-with-second-single-wannabe/','AOA To Make Their Comeback With Second Single “Wannabe”','Soompi','29 September 2012, 1:01 am','<p>After making their debut with <a href=\"http://www.soompi.com/2012/07/30/fnc-musics-new-girl-group-aoa-releases-debut-mv-for-elvis/\">&#8220;<strong>ELVIS</strong>&#8221; in the beginning of August</a>, rookie girl group <strong>AOA</strong> is already set to make their comeback with their second single &#8220;<strong>Wannabe</strong>.&#8221; Their teaser for &#8220;<strong>Get Out</strong>&#8221; was just revealed.</p>\n<div></div>\n<p>Their new single includes title track &#8220;Get Out,&#8221; &#8220;<strong>Happy Ending</strong>&#8221; and &#8220;<strong>My Song</strong>&#8221; for a total of three songs.</p>\n<p>Created by <strong>FNC Entertainment</strong>, the group immediately gained popularity for having a dance group and a band group.</p>\n<p>Their album cover was also recently revealed. In it, the girls are dressed up as popular characters from various movies. Can you guess which movies they are from? </p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-429827\" title=\"092812_aoa_2nd_album\" src=\"http://d1i45kki000yqu.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/092812_aoa_2nd_album.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"668\" /></p>\n<p>The girls also recently released a special greeting for the upcoming Chuseouk holiday.</p>\n<div></div>\n<p>&#8211;</p>',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(594,'http://www.soompi.com/2012/09/29/g-dragon-im-different-on-and-off-stage/','G-Dragon: “I’m Different On and Off Stage”','Soompi','29 September 2012, 12:08 am','<p>A journalist from SBS “<strong>E! Celebrity News</strong>” recently had a chance to sit down for an interview with <strong>G-Dragon</strong>.</p>\n<p>Q: Because you’re a highly anticipated singer, many people wondered what kind of color you would show through this album. What did you focus on this time around?<br />G-Dragon: I tried to be carefree and do things no one else can. If that could be a concept, I guess it’s my concept. I think I’m able to take in concepts that might not work or might be hard for others. That’s one of my strengths.</p>\n<p>Q: You’re known as a representative fashionista. There must be times when you feel burdened about this title.<br />G-Dragon: I’m very happy that I can wear what I want. During <strong>Big Bang</strong> promotions, I will have to coordinate with the other team members for a concept, but I’m able to wear whatever I want when I promote solo.</p>\n<p>Q: What do you do when you’re not promoting? I have a feeling that you know how to have a good time.<br />A: I’m very different from my onstage persona and when I’m offstage. When I’m out there performing, I’m confident and do my best to not look like I’m trying too hard. But when I get off the stage, as you can see now, my speech becomes slower and my thoughts and such are much like a child’s. When I’m not doing music&#8230; there’s nothing specific I do. I eat, meet up with friends and watch movies, hang out with guys and chat.”</p>\n<p>Soompiers, is there anyone who can pull off G-Dragon’s album concepts?</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-429707\" title=\"120928 gdragon inside\" src=\"http://d1i45kki000yqu.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/120928-gdragon-inside.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"683\" height=\"1024\" /></p>',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(595,'http://www.soompi.com/2012/09/28/trailer-for-smtown-live-in-tokyo-3d-revealed/','Trailer for SMTOWN Live in Tokyo 3D Revealed','Soompi','28 September 2012, 11:06 pm','<p>With <strong>SMTOWN Live in Toyko</strong> set to be released in theaters on October 11, they have revealed a trailer today on their official YouTube channel.</p>\n<p>Featuring <strong>BoA</strong>, <strong>DBSK</strong>, <strong>Super Junior</strong>, <strong>Girls&#8217; Generation</strong>, <strong>SHINee</strong>,<strong> f(x)</strong> , <strong>EXO</strong> and more, this special edition 3D movie will give fans an amazing close look at their performances. </p>\n<p> The performances were originally recorded in the Tokyo Dome last year on September 2 to 4 and saw an audience of over 150,000.</p>\n<div></div>',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(596,'http://www.soompi.com/2012/09/28/psy-releases-gangnam-style-mv-for-jill-stuart-new-york-dress-classy-project/','PSY Releases “Gangnam Style” MV for Jill Stuart New York Dress Classy Project','Soompi','28 September 2012, 10:06 pm','<p>As <strong>PSY</strong> has previously described <strong>&#8220;Gangnam Style</strong>&#8221; as &#8220;act classy, dance cheesy,&#8221; he has now collaborated with <strong>Jill Stuart New York</strong> for the &#8220;Dress Classy&#8221; project.  Today, he released a new music video for &#8220;Gangnam Style&#8221; featuring</p>\n<p>In the video, he arrives at a New York fashion party in a large limo. After performing his now iconic &#8220;horse dance&#8221; on the runway, the entire audience joins in with him. The lyrics &#8220;dress classy&#8221; have also been added to the song.    </p>\n<p>The video ends with a &#8220;to be continued&#8230;&#8221; and a QR code that leads to the <a href=\"http://www.jillstuartny.co.kr/front/jill_ny/m/main.html\">Korean web site</a> for Jill Stuart New York. </p>\n<div></div>\n<div><span>-</span></div>\n<div>What did you think of this new &#8220;Gangnam Style&#8221; music video? Are there too many versions out now?</div>',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(597,'http://www.soompi.com/2012/09/28/g-na-recently-transforms-into-a-sexy-secretary/','G.NA Recently Transforms Into a Sexy Secretary','Soompi','28 September 2012, 9:27 pm','<p>Is it getting hot in here?<strong> G.NA</strong>’s making sure no one is cold this coming winter.</p>\n<p>On September 27, she uploaded a picture on her twitter with the caption, “This is one of the cuts from the <strong>Lefee</strong> photo shoot. OMG. The comments I get from people around me are teacher, researcher, office worker and&#8230; ah&#8230;ah.. ahjumma? Just a little bit? How is this change?”</p>\n<p>In the picture, she’s wearing a fashionable white top. Her medium brown hair is up in a bun, but she left her bangs covering her forehead. She wears brown horn rimmed glasses and holds a tablet to complete the secretary look.</p>\n<p>Netizens who saw the picture commented, “I’ve been wondering what you have been up to. I see that you’re shooting CF’s,” “Man, the body is daebak,” “Can a secretary be so sexy?”</p>\n<p>Soompiers, who else do you think would make a sexy secretary?</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-429692\" title=\"120928 gna inside\" src=\"http://d1i45kki000yqu.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/120928-gna-inside.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"520\" height=\"526\" /></p>',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(598,'http://www.soompi.com/2012/09/28/kim-tae-woo-reveals-mv-teaser-for-looking-at-myself-makes-me-sad/','Kim Tae Woo Reveals MV Teaser for “Looking at Myself Makes Me Sad”','Soompi','28 September 2012, 8:16 pm','<p><strong>Kim Tae Woo</strong> teaser for his new sing &#8220;<strong>Looking at Myself Makes Me Sad</strong>&#8221; was revealed online today.</p>\n<p>In the teaser video, we see actor <strong>Ryu Seung Bum</strong> with broken glasses, standing in a room that was torn apart. As the camera zooms in on his face, he grins for a moment before returning to a serious look.</p>\n<p>Set for release next week on October 4, the single is a special collaboration with producing team <strong>Duble Sikekick</strong>. Kim Tae Woo&#8217;s new song is said to be the first of many collaborations that will appear in their upcoming project album. Duble Sidekick consists of rapper <strong>Park Jang Geun</strong> and <strong>Oneway</strong>&#8216;s <strong>Chance</strong>. Some of their recent hit songs include <strong>MBLAQ</strong>&#8216;s &#8220;<strong>It&#8217;s War</strong>,&#8221; <strong>Baek Ji Young</strong>&#8216;s &#8220;<strong>Good Boy</strong>&#8221; and <strong>SISTAR</strong>&#8216;s &#8220;<strong>Loving U</strong>.&#8221;   </p>\n<div></div>\n<p>Exited for Kim Tae Woo&#8217;s comeback? We sure are!</p>',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(599,'http://www.soompi.com/2012/09/28/new-girl-group-goddess-releases-debut-mv-farewell-party/','New Girl Group Goddess Releases Debut MV “Farewell Party”  + Dance Practice','Soompi','28 September 2012, 7:11 pm','<p>With the release of their debut single today, new girl group <strong>Goddess</strong> has now revealed their music video for &#8220;<strong>Farewell Party</strong>.&#8221; </p>\n<p>While the song is an electronic hip-hop track, the music video features many closeups of the members along with various motorcycle action scenes.</p>\n<p>Goddess’ four members are <strong>Yejin</strong>, <strong>Bitna</strong>, <strong>Sojeong</strong> and <strong>Eunjee</strong>. The group was created by <strong>KW Entertainment</strong> along with <strong>Def Company</strong>, which focuses on dance, vocal and rap training. The song was also made by <strong>Yang Sun Kyu</strong>, the CEO of Def Company.   </p>\n<p>According their their video description, &#8220;the name GODDESS comes from the word goddess to show how great woman are, and it also shows the group&#8217;s goal to become the best.&#8221;</p>\n<div></div>\n<p>Dance Practice</p>\n<div></div>\n<p>What did you think of their debut music video? With many groups coming out this year, do you think they will be able to stand out?</p>',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0),
