	(664,'http://www.engadget.com/2012/09/28/nexus-7-google-play-credit-promo-ending/','PSA: $25 Google Play credit for Nexus 7 ends this weekend','Engadget','28 September 2012, 11:44 pm','<p> <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2012/09/28/nexus-7-google-play-credit-promo-ending/\"><img alt=\"PSA $25 Google Play credit for Nexus 7 ends this weekend\" data-src-height=\"399\" data-src-width=\"600\" src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2012/09/nexus7928.jpg\" /></a></p><p> Those who have been keeping a close eye on Google\'s 7-inch, <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2012/06/28/android-4-1-jelly-bean-review-a-look-at-whats-changed-in-googl/\">Jelly Bean-loaded</a> Nexus 7 would know that the company kindly <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2012/06/27/google-nexus-7-25-dollar-credit/\">includes 25 bucks</a> worth of Play credit with any purchase of said tablet. Unfortunately, as the famed <span>clich&eacute;</span> would tell us, all good things must come to an end -- and, well, such is the case with this neat promotion, which will expire on Sunday, September 30th. Here\'s the good news, however: there\'s still a relatively good amount of time for folks interested to get it on the <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2012/03/06/google-play-replaces-android-market/\">Google Play</a> deal, so now would be the perfect moment to snag what some are calling <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2012/06/28/nexus-7-review/\">the best $200 tablet</a> -- and who knows, this might even lead to a post-order <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2012/09/27/caption-contest-eric-schmidt-does-gangnam-style-with-psy/\">Gangnam Style celebration</a> of your own.</p><p>Filed under: <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/category/misc/\" rel=\"tag\">Misc</a>, <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/category/tablets/\" rel=\"tag\">Tablets</a>, <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/category/google/\" rel=\"tag\">Google</a></p><p><a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2012/09/28/nexus-7-google-play-credit-promo-en